  "sections": [
    {
      "id": "section_1",
      "title": "Background",
      "content": [
        "The policy space ofsymmetric zero-sum Game-of-Skillsis composed oftransitive skill dimensionsandintransitive strategic cycles.",
        "Solving intransitive strategy games:Game-theoretic population learning algorithms (e.g. FP, PSRO) offer convergence guarantees to an NE, where each policy best-responds to a mixture over predecessors.",
        "However, when combined with modern deep RL techniques, population learning comes at significantcosts, for two reasons:",
        "Lack of positive transfer across policies;",
        "Suboptimal \"good\"-responses populating the policy population;",
        "Can we leverage the expressiveness of modern deep NNs to enable asinglemodel to explore, represent and reason about diverse strategies while retaining game theoretic guarantees using the same infrastructure as \"self-play\"?"
      ],
